parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak and Vapor Leak from Fuel Tank and Fuel Pump
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel leak and vapor leak can cause a fire hazard, especially when the vehicle is parked in a closed garage or driven with a full tank of fuel. This can lead to serious accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: wet areas around the fuel tank
and fuel droplets on the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Valve guide failure can cause the valve to drop into the cylinder, leading to engine failure, loss of power, and potential accidents or fires.
Clutch hydraulic system failure can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump/fuel tank cracks can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to accidents or fires.
The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on or comes on intermittently
indicating a fault in the airbag system
which may be affected by the positioning of the passenger seat
